   <conbody>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <note class="- topic/note ">The bypass mains needs to be available
and within tolerance. The static switch EN needs to be available.
The switch over does not interrupt the load.</note>
            <p class="- topic/p ">To switch between
bypass operation and normal operation:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Hash key</b> to enter the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b>. </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Use the arrow keys to navigate to <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To turn on: </b>Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Clock/number 1 key</b> to switch
from normal operation to bypass operation. The load is now supplied
by the bypass mains via the static switch EN.</p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">To turn off: </b>Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Star/number 0 key</b> to switch from bypass operation
to normal operation. The load is now supplied by the inverter.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Back key</b> or wait 30 seconds to exit the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b>.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
